criar um iam,grupo de seguran√ßa e vpc , logo apos uma ec2(maquina ubuntu) e associar a um ip publico com elastic ip
criar uma runners no github associando essa ec2 ao github
e no prompt da ec2 digitar
Download
# Create a folder
$ mkdir actions-runner && cd actions-runner# Download the latest runner package
$ curl -o actions-runner-linux-x64-2.312.0.tar.gz -L https://github.com/actions/runner/releases/download/v2.312.0/actions-runner-linux-x64-2.312.0.tar.gz# Optional: Validate the hash
$ echo "85c1bbd104d539f666a89edef70a18db2596df374a1b51670f2af1578ecbe031  actions-runner-linux-x64-2.312.0.tar.gz" | shasum -a 256 -c# Extract the installer
$ tar xzf ./actions-runner-linux-x64-2.312.0.tar.gz
Configure
# Create the runner and start the configuration experience
$ ./config.sh --url https://github.com/Ruanfonseca/Sistema_servicePro --token APPWZGTRME26G3FPCBEYNZ3FXPJP4# Last step, run it!
$ ./run.sh
Using your self-hosted runner
# Use this YAML in your workflow file for each job
runs-on: self-hosted